main event: A housewife observed a lighted object hovering over a field before it suddenly disappeared in Dewey, Kansas in 1959.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a lighted object hovering over a field.
The witness felt concerned and asked a neighbor, but the neighbor did not see the object.
The witness was unable to identify the object.
Another report describes an object colored white, reflecting light, and changing shape from elliptical to circular, observed for 15 minutes in Tulsa, Oklahoma in 1960.
sighted object: a lighted object hovering over a field
